<set-var title="Meta-HTML Utility Programs">
<include header.mhtml>

<layout::page>
  <ptext>
    The following utilities are delivered with all <meta-html> products:

    <h3> Image Utilities </h3>
    <ul>
      <li> <a href="imagemap.mhtml"><b>imagemap</b></a>:
      A program which handles the server-side interpretation of clickable
      images.
    </ul>

    <h3> Database Utilities </h3>
    <ul>
      <li> <a href="dbdump.mhtml"><b>dbdump</b></a>:
      A program which prints out the contents of a <meta-html> database in
      human-readable form.

      <li> <a href="dbpack.mhtml"><b>dbpack</b></a>:
      A program which converts a <meta-html> database from a binary format
      to an ASCII representation, or from an ACSII representation to a
      binary format.

      <li> <a href="dbcreate.mhtml"><b>dbcreate</b></a>:
      A program which creates a <meta-html> packed database from an ASCII
      text file containing comma-separated fields.  This program uses a
      <i>description file</i> to control the way in which the text file is
      interpreted, and of the created database.
    </ul>

    <h3> Session Utilities </h3>
    <ul>
      <li> <a href="list-sessions.mhtml"><b>list-sessions</b></a>:
      A program which displays the existing sessions in the session database.

      <li> <a href="delete-session.mhtml"><b>delete-session</b></a>:
      A program which allows you to manually delete an active session.

      <li> <a href="set-session-timeout.mhtml"><b>set-session-timeout</b></a>:
      A program which allows you to manually set the timeout for a
      particular session directly from the command line.

      <li> <a href="get-session-var.mhtml"><b>get-session-var</b></a>:
      A program which returns the value of a variable for a specific session.

      <li> <a href="set-session-var.mhtml"><b>set-session-var</b></a>:
      A program which set the value of a variable for a specific session.

      <li> <a href="gc-database.mhtml"><b>gc-database</b></a>:
      A program which reorganizes the session database information, thus
      reducing the amount of disk space that it uses.  This program should
      be run periodically, depending on your site and usage.

      <li> <a href="reap-sessions.mhtml"><b>reap-sessions</b></a>:
      A program which immediately removes sessions which have timed out
      from the session database.  This program is rarely used, since
      reaping happens automatically whenever a new session is created.
    </ul>

    <h3> Miscellaneous Utilities </h3>
    <ul>
      <li> <a href="strip-tags.mhtml"><b>strip-tags</b></a>:
      A program which filters out every HTML and <meta-html> tag from its
      input.  Very useful in conjunction when creating search databases, or
      to produce a text file from an HTML or <meta-html> input file.

      <li> <a href="mklib.mhtml"><b>mklib</b></a>
      A <Meta-HTML> script which creates a <i>library</i> file from a
      number of input source files.
    </ul>
  </ptext>
</layout::page>

